    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> How can you use javascript in 3.0 then? For example javascipts for plots.\n\nYou can still use javascript, it will be displayed on execution or if the notebook is trusted (see below). \nWe cannot afford to run javascript when you download a notebook as it might contain something along\n\n```\nIPython.kernel.execute(\"sytem.exec 'rm -rf --no-preserve-root /'\")\n```\n\nThus there is a  mechanism of notebook signing that will allow the non-sanitisation of HTML only if the signature is valid. You can still go to file menu and explicitly trust the notebook if you like. If you don't explicitely trust a notebook, then you have to rerun each codecell at least once for the notebook to get trusted by you.\n\nDoes that makes sens ?  \n"
  },
